name: 12ga 00 Buckshot
description: A standard 00 buckshot ammunition, consisting of multiple large pellets and designed for close-range engagements. Although it may have slightly wider shot patterns compared to the FC 00 Buckshot, it still delivers significant kinetic energy.

name: 12ga Slug
description: Shotgun slugs are single-projectile ammunition designed for increased accuracy and penetration compared to buckshot. They consist of a large, solid projectile (.68 to .72 caliber) that delivers high kinetic energy upon impact.

name: 12ga SST Sabot Slug
description: SST Sabot Slugs use a plastic carrier to hold a smaller, high-velocity projectile (.50 caliber or smaller). When fired, the sabot separates from the projectile, enabling it to travel at high speed and deliver significant energy upon impact.

name: 12ga FC 00 Buckshot
description: The Flight Control 00 Buckshot ammunition is designed to provide tighter shot patterns and increased accuracy, making it highly effective for close-range engagements. The flight control wad helps to maintain a more consistent shot spread, improving hit probability on target.

name: 5.45x39mm FMJ
description: The 5.45x39mm FMJ ammunition is a military cartridge designed for rifles such as the AK-74. It features a full metal jacket design with a lead core encased in copper, providing reliable feeding and penetration. This ammunition is widely used in military applications due to its consistent performance in both combat and training scenarios.

name: 5.45x39mm HP
description: The 5.45x39mm Hollow Point (HP) ammunition is engineered for rifles such as the AK-74. Its hollow point design is intended to expand upon impact, creating larger wound channels and increased stopping power. As a result, 5.45x39mm HP ammo is suitable for certain self-defense and hunting applications, providing effective terminal ballistics.

name: 5.45x39mm PS (7N6)
description: The 5.45x39mm PS (7N6) ammunition is a military cartridge used in rifles such as the AK-74. The 'PS' designation refers to the projectile's steel-core design, which enhances its penetration capabilities. This ammunition is widely adopted for military use due to its armor-piercing properties and is commonly used in military training and combat scenarios.

name: 5.45x39mm PP (7N10)
description: The 5.45x39mm PP (7N10) ammunition is a specialized military cartridge designed for rifles like the AK-74. It features a steel core for improved penetration capabilities, making it suitable for armor-piercing applications. This ammo is known for its effectiveness in military use, particularly in scenarios where enhanced penetration is a priority.

name: 5.45x39mm US (7U1)
description: The 5.45x39mm US gs round contains a subsonic 5.1-gram bullet with a pointed tungsten carbide core over a lead base enclosed in a bimetallic jacket. It is housed in a steel case with a reduced charge. This US cartridge was developed by TsNIITochMash in the mid-80s for use in the AKS-74UB and AKS-74UBN.

name: 5.45x39mm BP (7N22)
description: The 5.45x39mm BP (7N22) ammunition is a specialized cartridge designed for rifles like the AK-74. It features a ballistic projectile with an armor-piercing steel core, making it highly effective at penetrating armored targets.  This ammo is widely used in military applications where penetrating protective barriers is essential.

name: 5.45x39mm BT (7BT4)
description: The 5.45x39mm BT (7BT4) cartridge is specifically crafted for rifles like the AK-74. The designation 'BT' originates from the Russian term 'Boytsovaya Tip,' meaning 'Armor-Piercing.' Featuring a pointed steel core embedded within the projectile, the 7BT4 variant excels in penetrating armor. Widely adopted in military settings, this ammunition offers enhanced penetration capabilities, rendering it highly effective against armored targets. It serves as the preferred option in combat situations where overcoming protective barriers is imperative.

name: 5.45x39mm BS (7N24)
description: The 5.45x39mm BS (7N24) cartridge is designed for rifles such as the AK-74. The designation 'BS' stands for 'Broneboinaya Snaiper' or 'Armor-Piercing Sniper' round. It contains a hardened steel core that enhances its armor-piercing capabilities. The 5.45x39mm BS (7N24) ammunition is commonly used in military applications due to its effectiveness against armored targets. Ideal for sniper and designated marksman roles, the cartridge excels in scenarios demanding precise penetration.

name: 5.45x39 PPBS (7N39)
description: The 5.45x39mm PPBS (7N39) ammunition is a specialized cartridge designed for rifles like the AK-74. The "PPBS" designation stands for "Povishennaya Probivaemost Broneboinaya Snaryad" in Russian, which translates to "Increased Armor-Piercing Projectile." This advanced round features a hardened steel core designed for exceptional armor-piercing capabilities. Widely used in military applications, the 5.45x39mm PPBS (7N39) ammo is recognized for its effectiveness against armored targets, making it suitable for situations where superior penetration is essential.

name: 5.56x45mm AP (M855)
description: A commonly used military round designed for rifles chambered in the 5.56x45mm caliber. It features a 62-grain projectile with a steel penetrator tip and a lead core. The M855 is known for its improved penetration capabilities, particularly against light armor and barriers. It is a full metal jacket (FMJ) round with a green-painted tip for easy identification.

name: 5.56x45mm Tracer (M856)
description: A military round designed for rifles chambered in the 5.56x45mm caliber. It features a 63.7-grain projectile with a red-colored tip and a lead core. The M856 is a tracer round that allows for visual tracking of the bullet's trajectory during daylight conditions.

name: 5.56x45mm AP (M855A1)
description: A specialized military round used in rifles chambered for the 5.56x45mm caliber. It is an improved variant of the M855 round with enhanced performance and penetration capabilities. The M855A1 features a 62-grain projectile with a steel penetrator tip and a lead-free copper core. It is designed to provide increased accuracy, consistency, and improved barrier penetration compared to its predecessor.

name: 5.56x45mm Tracer (M856A1)
description: A military-grade round designed for use in rifles chambered for the 5.56x45mm caliber. The M856A1 incorporates advancements in tracer technology and features a more consistent and brighter trace compared to the M856.

name: 5.56x45 M995
description: A 5.56x45mm armor-piercing cartridge with a hardened steel penetrator core encased in a copper jacket. The M995 is specifically developed to provide enhanced penetration capabilities against armored targets, including vehicles and personnel wearing body armor.

name: 5.56x45mm FMJ
description: A 5.56x45mm full metal jacket cartridge with a lead-core bullet encased in a steel case. The jacket enables a higher muzzle velocity, and the bullet can penetrate basic ballistic armor. However, the cartridge has a lower capacity to expand after impact, which reduces the damage to the target.

name: 5.56x45mm HPBT
description: A hollow-point, boat-tailed 5.56x45mm cartridge with a lead-core bullet designed for high accuracy and rapid post-impact expansion. The boat tail shape of the bullet reduces drag and enhances stability in flight, resulting in better accuracy and extended effective range. This cartridge is primarily used for long-range hunting.

name: 5.56x45mm FMJ (M193)
description: A standard 5.56x45mm military cartridge featuring a lead-core, full metal jacket bullet enclosed in a brass case. The M193 is known for its reliable performance and balanced ballistics, offering good accuracy, moderate recoil, and reliable feeding in various firearms.

name: 5.56x45mm SP
description: The 5.56x45mm SP ammunition features a soft point (SP) bullet design, which offers improved expansion upon impact compared to full metal jacket rounds. This can result in greater tissue damage, making the SP round effective for hunting and self-defense applications.

name: 7.62x25mm FMJ
description: The 7.62×25mm Tokarev FMJ (Full Metal Jacket) ammunition is a powerful pistol cartridge originally designed for the Soviet TT-33 pistol and later used in various firearms, including submachine guns. Developed in the early 1930s, it features a bottlenecked cartridge case with a diameter of 7.62mm and a length of 25mm. The 7.62×25mm Tokarev round is prized for its penetration capabilities and has seen extensive military and civilian use in Eastern Europe and Asia.

name: 7.62x25mm Pst
description: The 7.62x25mm Pst ammunition commonly features a bullet with a steel core, which enhances the penetration capabilities of the round, making it effective against various types of targets, including body armor and light cover. Additionally, the use of a steel core can contribute to the ammunition's armor-piercing capabilities.

name: 7.62x25mm PT
description: The 7.62x25mm PT is a tracer round specifically designed for target designation and fire adjustment during combat situations, but lacks the penetration and stopping power of standard FMJ rounds.

name: 7.62x39mm PS (57-N-231C)
description: A 7.62x39mm cartridge with a steel-core bullet encased in a bimetallic steel and copper case. It was designed in 1943 and has undergone various enhancements, but remains in widespread use today. At a distance of 300m, it can penetrate a 6mm thick steel plate. The PS designation stands for Pulya Stalnaya, which translates to Steel Bullet.

name: 7.62x39mm BP (7N23)
description: The 7.62x39mm 7N23 (BP) ammunition is a specialized cartridge designed for rifles such as the AK-47. It features a ballistic projectile with a steel core, making it effective against armored targets. This ammo is widely used in military applications due to its enhanced penetration capabilities and is employed in scenarios where defeating protective barriers is crucial.

name: 7.62x39mm Tracer (57-N-231P)
description: The 7.62x39mm 57-N-231P Tracer ammunition is intended for rifles such as the AK-47. It includes a pyrotechnic tracer element that produces a visible light trail during flight, aiding in tracking. This ammunition is mainly used for training and signaling, combining standard 7.62x39mm features with tracer technology.

name: 7.62x39mm US
description: The 7.62x39mm US ammunition is a variant of the widely used cartridge for rifles such as the AK-47. The 'US' designation indicates adherence to U.S. specifications. It is known for its reliability and is used in both military and civilian applications worldwide.

name: 7.62x39mm SP
description: A 7.62x39mm soft point cartridge with a lead core semi-jacketed bullet. It is designed to expand after impact, causing massive damage to the target at the cost of reduced penetration.

name: 7.62x39 57-BZ-231 (BZ)
description: 7.62mm cartridge 1943 model with armour piercing incendiary 7.62 BZ and incendiary 7.62 Z bullets were produced till to the beginning 1960 years. The cartridges was intended for light armouring targets defeat, fuel ignition which is being behind the armours or in thick-walled container and also for military personnel defeat which are being behind light armoured coverings.

name: 7.62x51mm FMJ (M80)
description: The 7.62x51mm NATO M80 cartridge is widely used for military and civilian applications due to its reliability and solid performance.

name: 7.62x51mm FMJ (M80A1)
description: The 7.62x51mm M80A1 consistently delivers excellent fragmentation, effective armor penetration, and barrier-blind characteristics.

name: 7.62x51mm AP (M61)
description: The 7.62x51mm (M61) armor-piercing cartridge is specifically designed to penetrate armor due to its pointed steel core. It is commonly used in military applications because of its enhanced penetration capability, which makes it effective against armored targets.

name: 7.62x51mm Tracer (M62)
description: This tracer cartridge conforms to NATO standards and is comparable to the M62. It features a luminous trace that extends up to 775 meters from the muzzle, visible during both day and night, making it suitable for all 7.62x51mm firearms.

name: 7.62x51mm HPBT
description: The .308 Winchester (308 WIN.) ammunition with Hollow Point Boat Tail (HPBT) combines precision and terminal performance. The HPBT bullet is designed for accuracy and enhances stability in flight, making it a favored choice for precision shooting and hunting applications.

name: 7.62x54R Tracer (T-46M)
description: The T-46M Tracer cartridge is a modernized ammunition designed for the Mosin-Nagant rifle. It has a distinctive green-painted tip and features a smokeless, nitrocellulose-based powder (VT) that propels a 9.5-9.8g bullet at a muzzle velocity of 825-855m/s. The bullet is clad in a tombac-plated steel shell and has a lead core with 1-2% antimony for enhanced performance.

name: 7.62x54R Sniper Round (7N1)
description: The 7N1 cartridge is a preferred choice for snipers due to its precision. It has a length ranging from 75.91 to 77.16mm and features a smokeless, nitrocellulose-based powder marked as ВТ. This propels a 9.52-9.56g bullet at speeds of 820-835m/s from the SVD rifle. The bullet is enveloped in a tombac-plated steel shell and houses a St 10 core weighing 2.2-2.3g. This cartridge is ideal for long-range accuracy and delivers consistent performance for sniper applications.

name: 7.62x54R LPS (57-N-323S)
description: The 57-N-323S (GZh) cartridge features the iconic LPS (Light Armor-Piercing, Steel-Core) bullet. This cartridge is known for its lethal combination of a St 10 steel core and a 9.45-9.75g bullet, and can be recognized by its silver-painted tip, a tradition observed from 1953 to 1978.

name: 7.62x54R AP (7N13)
description: The 7.62x54R 7N13 cartridge is a powerful armor-piercing (AP) round designed for precision and penetration. It has a distinctive purple tip and provides reliable armor-penetrating capabilities, making it an excellent choice for applications requiring enhanced piercing power.

name: 7.65 Browning Xtreme Defender
description: The 7.65 Browning 55gr. Xtreme Defender ammunition has a solid copper projectile with flutes and sharp edges penetrating deeply and creating temporary and permanent wound cavities. Compared to traditional JHP rounds, Xtreme Defender rounds provide better penetration and terminal performance.

name: 7.65 Browning FMJ
description: The 7.65 Browning FMJ ammunition has a full metal jacket projectile, usually with a lead core covered in a copper or other metal jacket. These rounds are intended for general-purpose use, providing good penetration and reliability, but they may not have the terminal ballistics of specialized hollow point or defensive rounds.

name: 7.65 Browning JHP
description: The 7.65 Browning JHP ammunition utilizes a hollow point projectile that expands upon impact, creating larger wound channels and maximizing stopping power. These rounds are commonly used in self-defense and law enforcement applications where terminal performance is crucial.

name: 9x19mm FMJ
description: A 9mm Parabellum cartridge loaded with a full metal jacket (FMJ) bullet. It features a lead core encapsulated by a copper or brass jacket, providing smooth feeding and reliable performance. The FMJ design prevents the bullet from expanding upon impact, making it suitable for target shooting, training, and general-purpose use.

name: 9x19mm Tracer
description: A specialized type of the 9mm Parabellum (9x19mm) cartridge that contains a tracer compound in the bullet. This allows the bullet to emit visible light during flight, making it useful for tracking the bullet's trajectory in low-light conditions or for training purposes.

name: 9x19mm HP
description: A 9mm Parabellum cartridge loaded with a hollow point bullet. Unlike full metal jacket (FMJ) rounds, hollow point ammunition is designed to expand upon impact, creating a larger wound channel and transferring more energy to the target.

name: 9x19 Libra Snail
description: The Snail ammunition was created in 2002 and made its debut at the IWA (Internationale Waffenausstellung), a firearms exhibition held in Nuremberg, Germany, in 2003. The round's designer, Vlastimil Libra, utilized a bullet made of solid brass or aluminum with a steel core to achieve controlled deformation in the projectile. This unique combination of materials and construction results in a round with exceptional penetration capabilities.

name: 9x19 RIP
description: The 9mm G2 Research RIP 96gr. HP LF (High Performance Lead-Free) Ammo is a cutting-edge ammunition designed for self-defense. It features a distinctive Radically Invasive Projectile (RIP) design with a precision-machined copper hollow point. The unique construction promotes controlled expansion upon impact, creating devastating wound channels.

name: 9x19mm Xtreme Penetrator P+
description: The Xtreme Penetrator Ammo is designed to provide superior penetration and stopping power. It features a 115-grain solid copper bullet with a unique fluted design that maintains its structural integrity and delivers deep penetration upon impact. The +P designation indicates higher pressure, resulting in increased velocity and energy transfer. This ammunition is ideal for self-defense scenarios where reliable barrier penetration is crucial.

name: CZ 4M Lancer
description: The CZ 4M Lancer offers advanced ballistic protection for high-risk operations. With its unique anatomic design, it ensures optimal weight distribution between the operator's back and torso, reducing shoulder strain during extended wear.

name: Spitfire Plate Carrier
description: Used by the GROM Polish special forces, the Spitfire, taking its name from the iconic World War II fighter plane, is a lightweight and highly customizable plate carrier that offers advanced ballistic protection.

name: M2 Plate Carrier
description: This versatile plate carrier is used by the National Guard of Russia. Offering excellent protection while remaining compact and lightweight, the M2 features a modular design that allows for easy customization and adjustment to accommodate different mission requirements and gear setups.

name: 6B45 Ratnik
description: A part of the Ratnik infantry combat system. It is designed to provide comprehensive ballistic protection and versatility for soldiers in modern warfare scenarios. The 6B45 Ratnik features integrated ceramic plates and soft armor materials, offering effective defense against bullets and fragments.

name: Specter
description: With its streamlined and low-profile design, the Specter plate carrier offers a discreet and efficient platform for carrying plates during surveillance operations.

name: Pantsir 2.0
description: The Pantsir 2.0 is a Russian plate carrier compatible with 265x 340mm SAPI, ESAPI, and Granit plates, featuring additional soft armor. It provides ballistic defense against threats in high-risk operational environments and can be fitted with climatic inserts that reduce sweating and increase the wearer's comfort.

name: CGPC3 TQS
description: A low-profile, lightweight, and fully modular plate carrier made in the Czech Republic. With its sturdy construction and advanced materials, it offers reliable defense against ballistic threats and fragmentation, while its Tube Quick System allows for comfortable and silent unfastening.

name: Recon Plate Carrier
description: A lightweight and versatile low-profile plate carrier offering enhanced mobility without compromising protection. It is trusted by professionals for its durability and adaptability, making it an ideal choice for those facing dynamic and challenging environments.

name: Chest Rig 901 Elite 4
description: A high-performance and versatile tactical gear designed to provide efficient load-carrying capabilities for military and law enforcement. This version allows for a ballistic plate to be worn in its wider upper section, while still enabling the user to get in and out of the rig at speed and without any assistance.

name: LBT-6094 G3v2
description: A third-generation variant of the LBT-6094 plate carrier series, tailored to provide enhanced performance and functionality for military, law enforcement, and tactical operators. Featuring a rugged and lightweight construction, the LBT-6094 G3v2 offers reliable ballistic protection with integrated pockets for ballistic plates.

name: Delta Backpack
description: The Delta Backpack boasts a substantial 65-liter capacity, making it a spacious and reliable choice for various operational demands. Despite its size, the backpack prioritizes comfort with adjustable padded straps with soft foam lining and elastic pads for added support, ensuring ergonomic wear during extended missions or outdoor activities.

name: Drawstring Backpack

name: Gunfigter 14
description: A tactical and compact backpack designed for users who require a balance between storage capacity and mobility. It offers a versatile option for carrying essential gear during short missions, outdoor activities, or everyday use.

name: Small Tourist Backpack
description: A small basic backpack designed for light outdoor activities. With a modest capacity, it offers a convenient option for carrying essentials during short trips or hikes.

name: Sport Backpack
description: A functional backpack designed for daily use. With a basic design, it offers a convenient option for carrying personal belongings during everyday activities.

name: JDEN Jam Ball
description: Popular among outdoor enthusiasts, the JDEN Jam Ball backpack strikes a balance between functionality and portability. Its compact design and durability make it a reliable choice for those seeking a versatile bag that can adapt to various situations and provide essential storage capacity.

name: Assault Backpack
description: Constructed from durable materials, the Assault Backpack provides ample storage space for items such as ammunition, communication devices, tactical gear, and personal accessories. Its design is focused on efficiency and reliability in demanding environments.

name: Scorpion OCP Convoy Pack
description: A military-style backpack designed for tactical and operational use. It offers a rugged and efficient solution for carrying gear and equipment during missions, field operations, and deployments while also featuring compatibility with hydration systems and MOLLE webbing for the attachment of additional pouches.

name: AMP12

name: Patrol Backpack

name: Falang 28
description: A large civillian backpack for individuals seeking substantial storage capacity for their daily needs. It offers a reliable solution for carrying personal belongings, essentials, and even larger items during various activities.

name: Large Tourist Bag
description: A large tourist backpack perfect for longer treks. It can fit all the necessities for camping, including a sleeping bag and a tent.

name: Rush 100
description: The Rush 100 is a high-capacity tactical backpack designed for versatile use. It offers ample storage space across multiple compartments for gear, equipment, and supplies. Featuring MOLLE webbing, it allows for customization with additional pouches and accessories. Padded shoulder straps, adjustable chest and waist straps, and a comfortable back panel ensure comfortable wear.

name: Rush 72 2.0
description: A robust and highly versatile tactical pack built for extended missions and outdoor adventures. With a spacious 55-liter capacity, multiple compartments, and MOLLE webbing, it offers ample storage and customizable organization.

name: Commander (Navy)
description: The Commander Series 1 provides good protection against ballistic threats and fragmentation, featuring a Cordura carrier for enhanced durability and fully adjustable waist and shoulder straps for a perfect fit.

name: Commander (Black)

name: Kasem Chocolate Wafers
description: Delicately layered with luscious chocolate, these exquisite crispy wafers will have you yearning for more after every delicious crunch. Kasem Chocolate wafers are a registered trademark of the Kasem styrofoam company.

name: TamTam DoubleChoc
description: This exclusive candy bar offers double the amount of rich cocoa, providing a satisfying chocolate experience with each bite.

name: Windmill Almond Chocolate Bar
description: A symphony of silky chocolate and crispy almonds, carefully crafted to provide a delightful combination of tastes and textures, perfect for your sweet cravings.

name: Lychee in Syrup
description: Sweet lychee fruits preserved in a simple, syrupy solution, offering a taste of tropical goodness in every bite.

name: Canned Tuna Chunks
description: Dive into a world of ocean-inspired flavors with these exquisite tuna chunks, gently packed in natural coconut water. A unique combination that offers a fresh, wholesome taste. Now with even less mercury!

name: Cowboy Baked Beans
description: Savor the zesty kick of these hearty baked beans, simmered in a tangy and spicy tomato sauce. A taste of the Wild West that adds a fiery twist to your meal.

name: Mackerel in Teriyaki Sauce
description: Tender mackerel fillets bathed in a delicious teriyaki sauce, presenting a harmonious blend of sweet and savory flavors.

name: HDR Meal
description: Humanitarian Daily Ration. A ration pack designed to provide essential daily sustenance to individuals in need, offering a balanced selection of nourishing food items to support their well-being.

name: Metal Container
description: A strange metal container of unknown origin. It's slightly warm to the touch.

name: Box of Supplies
description: A box full of various items intended to bring relief to the locals.

name: GPS Tracker
description: A device that uses satellite signals to determine and record the precise location of an object or person. Commonly used for vehicle tracking or personal safety.

name: Briefcase
description: A briefcase assumably full of money. Great for making new friends.

name: Kanoa's Camera
description: The last viewed photo on this camera is of Kanoa and his family.

name: Weird Book
description: A book filled with strange drawings and cryptic symbols. Looks that it's bound in human flesh and inked in blood, but it's probably just faux leather and red ink.

name: Case with a Revolver
description: This case contains an exquisite work of art in the form of a deadly weapon.

name: Goodbye Letter
description: This letter contains heartfelt goodbye and an explanation of the man's actions - he offered himself as a human target in order to provide for his family.

name: Intelligence Folder
description: A folder containing info about some sort of arms deal between the local criminal elements and the LAF.

name: Security Footage
description: This footage identifies the current inhabitants of YBL-1 as the Lamang Liberation Army.

name: Prisoner Info Folder
description: This folder contains information on the prisoner. He was processed here and transported to an unknown location.

name: Camera Wiretap
description: A device that can be used to tap into any survaillance stream.

name: Poison Vial
description: Contains a potent water-solluable toxin.

name: Army Codebook
description: This book contains information how to obtain decryptying keys.

name: Evacuation Orders
description: Contains orders to not let the majority of civilians evacuate. The reasoning for that is unknown.

name: Commander Details Folder
description: Details about the new commander of Fort Narith. It looks like he was appoointed just a few weeks prior to the Event, and is not from Lamang.

name: Army Medical Records
description: Contains medical records from Fort Narith.

name: Personal Folder
description: A personal folder of Nuon Bintang. Apparently, he used to be Fort Narith's former commander and was subsequently dishonorably discharged for a multitude of very shady deals.

name: Turncoat's Valuables
description: A briefcase full of non-specific valuables that allegedly belong to Turncoat.

name: Military Patrol Schedule
description: Contains all the patrol routes and assigned soldiers.

name: Arrest Warrant
description: An arrest warrant for Artisan's former colleague.

name: UNLRA Medical Supplies
description: This box contains various medical supplies used to support both the UNLRA and the local populace.

name: Flash Drive Containing Intel
description: This drive contains important information regarding the planned patrols of enemy forces.

name: Horrific Recordings
description: Contains inhumane scenes of torture and death.

name: Detonator Case
description: A case containing prepared detonators to be used with the fertilizer bombs.

name: Interrogation Orders
description: Contains orders to interogate an unknown PMC-affiliated prisoner. At the end, the folder contains information that the prisoner has escaped, and an order for recapture was given.

name: Interrogation Transcript
description: Details the little bits of information that were possible to be extracted from the stubborn prisoner. Apperently he belongs to a PMC operating from withing Ground Zero.

name: Guest List
description: This list contains names of guests and what services they purchased.

name: Precious Golf Club
description: Extremely valuable golf club. It is truly priceless.

name: Doctor's Diary
description: A diary of a local doctor who got left behind during the evacuation. A couple of the last entries mention a "female PMC medical officer" who was helping him by stashing supplies outside of the PMC base camp.

name: Kanoa Sinarath's Medallion
description: A gold-plated medallion which was given to Kanoa by his wife.

name: Convict's Notepad
description: A notepad belonging to one of the criminals who got left behind on the island.

name: Thug's Smartphone
description: A smartphone belonging to one of the criminals who got left behind on the island.

name: Bunker Computer Data
description: Floppy disks that carry valuable infromation. One carries label the "Distant Voice" written in cyrillic.

name: List of Orders
description: The flash drive contains orders for a foreign gang sent to Lamang to secure some kind of compromising materials.

name: VIP Program Info
description: Contains a "menu" of all the possible targets that can be shot at for the VIP's pleasure. The target can be then cooked and served for an extra fee.

name: Organisation Notes
description: Contains information about current gang activities.

name: List of Names
description: This note contains names of kindapped people who were being transported to various places. Namely the Midnight Sapphire and Tiger Bay "processing".

name: Tourist's Diary
description: Contains details on the tourist's plans and confirms her identity. She met some guys who like to party and got invited to their "special place." No more entries after that...

name: Jet Fighter Deal
description: This folder contains details of the exchange, the budget and the goods being traded. Somebody gained a lot of money from this deal, and the LAF got barely functional training jets.

name: Call up Papers
description: Call up papers for Atsawin Xiong. He is to report to Fort Narith ASAP.

name: Sample Collection Kit
description: This kit is used to safely collect various samples.

name: Lost Smartphone
description: Contains a lot of questionable materials and is not password protected.

name: Politican's Flashdrive
description: Whatever is recorded on this flashdrive is certainly illegal in most of the civilized world.

name: Client's Phone
description: Still contains a written but unsent message.

name: Fake Intel
description: Intel containing deceptive information to confuse the enemy and benefit the PMC.

name: Military Intel
description: Official documents from Fort Narith.

name: Precious Cigars
description: Very valuable cigars. Maybe no one will notice if you take one for a job well done?

name: Pile of Gold

name: Pilot Logbook
description: Contains all the routes undertaken by pilots in recent years.

name: Suspicious Box
description: Is it full of drugs? It's probably full of drugs, isn't it? Of course it's full of drugs...

name: Mercenary's Diary
description: Contains information about activities of the mercenary posing as a tourist. The last log is dated November 24 - the day of the Event.

name: Appeal to the Rebels
description: The drive contains recording of Artisan's appeal to stop hostilities with the PMC.

name: ELISA Testing Kit
description: Specialized tools for analyzing bodily fluids.

name: Artisan's Toolbox
description: An older set of tools that seems incredibly well-maintained. The inside of the box also reveals an old note that states, "For Laya, my love. One day you will fix this world."

name: UNLRA Medical Records
description: Contains information about the medical state of all the people entering the UNLRA refugee camp.

name: Client's Passport
description: A client's passport that needs to be delivered to Midnight Sapphire.

name: Transcript of an Interrogation
description: Transcript of the mechanic's interrogation. The military vehicles were beings sabotaged.

name: Soldier's Diary
description: The diary details the first days of the soldier's life in the Fort. The last entry mentions Ground Zero.

name: Turncoat's Box

name: UNLRA HQ Orders

name: List of Evacuees

name: Army Orders
description: The orders specify how to treat with the UN personel in transfers of unwanted people back out from the camp and into the hands of Lamang's army.

name: Flight Recorder
description: Flight recorder that has captured voices of the pilot and some valuable data from the fligth.

name: Mosin-Nagant Tri-Rail Scope Mount

name: M590 Picatinny Scope Rail

name: LEAP/01 Mount
description: A top-tier precision optic mount that delivers stability and repeatability. Constructed from advanced materials, the LEAP/01 is not only robust but also remarkably lightweight, minimizing additional weight on your firearm setup.

name: M590 Shockwave Quad Rail
description: This quad rail is designed to enhance the Mossberg 590 shotgun. Its durable construction provides a solid platform for attaching various tactical accessories while ensuring stability and accuracy during critical situations.

name: SKS Rear Sight Picatinny Rail

Designed for error-free installation, it's made of high-strength duralumin for a lasting performance.

The  "B-13N" rail above the receiver is an all-milled product made of D16T alloy with a black coating or desert color.
It is installed on the side tide ("dovetail") of the weapon and forms the Picatini bar, which does not overlap the line of the mechanical sight.

The adjustable IR illuminator offers a beam width from 1-105 mrad, making it perfect for target designation or flooding the night vision scene with illumination.

name: MAWL-C1

This beam offers substantial reach and peripheral illumination, making it well-suited for close to medium-range applications.

name: Surefire P1R Peacekeeper
description: The P1R Peacekeeper Tactical is a SureFire rechargeable light designed for law enforcement professionals and anyone in need of a high-quality flashlight. Its advanced LED and precise reflector deliver a 600-lumen high-output beam with impressive reach and peripheral illumination.

name: Surefire X300U-A
description: The Surefire X300U-A is a handgun flashlight that delivers 1,000 lumens of LED power. The precision TIR lens produces a powerful beam for close-to-medium-range engagements, while the ambidextrous switch and rugged aerospace aluminum body ensure effective threat identification and reliable performance in challenging conditions.

name: Surefire X400V-B-IRC

The device incorporates a Total Internal Reflection (TIR) lens with optically coated tempered glass, ensuring optimal light distribution and durability. name: AK-74M
description: The AK-74M, officially in service since 1991, is a modernized version of the AK-74. It is chambered in 5.45x39mm and is popular with military forces and armed groups worldwide. The 'M' designation indicates modern features, including a reinforced polymer folding stock for enhanced portability and maneuverability. The AK-74M can also include a side rail for attachments, enabling users to integrate different optics or accessories to meet mission requirements.

name: AK-74N
description: The AK-74N is a modified variant of the AK-74 rifle, designed with a side rail for attaching night vision scopes, indicated by the 'N' in its name. It is chambered in 5.45x39mm, offering improved accuracy and versatility, especially in low-light conditions. The side rail enables easy integration of night vision optics, allowing users to operate effectively during nighttime operations.

name: AKM
description: The AKM (Avtomat Kalashnikova Modernizirovanniy) was designed in 1959 as a successor to the renowned AK-47. It represents a significant advancement in the evolution of the AK series of rifles, as it was specifically engineered to streamline manufacturing processes, making it more cost-effective and easier to produce on a large scale. The AKM, chambered in 7.62x39mm, became the standard rifle for the Soviet Army and was widely adopted by most member states of the Warsaw Pact, ensuring its presence across Eastern Europe and beyond. It was exported and produced in many other countries, making it ubiquitous worldwide.

name: AKMN
description: The AKMN is a variant of the AKM that comes equipped with a side rail for use with night vision scopes, as denoted by the 'N' in its name. This model is a popular choice among military forces and armed groups worldwide due to its improved accuracy and versatility.

name: AKMSN
description: The AKMSN is a customized version of the AKMS automatic rifle. It has a dovetail mount for the NSP family of night vision scopes, making it adaptable for low-light conditions and improving visibility during nighttime operations. The foldable stock adds to its practicality and ease of transportation.

name: M4A1
description: The M4A1, in service since 1994, is a fully automatic variant of the M4 carbine widely utilized by U.S. special operations forces. This highly regarded rifle offers exceptional performance and reliability, with a selective fire system that allows operators to switch between semi-automatic and fully automatic modes. Its compact size, collapsible stock, and compatibility with various accessories make it ideal for close-quarters combat and versatile for various mission requirements.

name: MK18
description: The MK18 is a high-quality AR-15 build approach developed by Daniel Defense. It is considered one of the best-quality AR-15 builds on the market due to its precise construction and tight tolerances, which make it very reliable and well-performing. The MK18 is also fielded by US Rangers.

name: Glock 17
description: The Glock 17 is a renowned semi-automatic pistol chambered in 9x19mm Parabellum, designed and manufactured by Glock GmbH. It has gained widespread recognition for its exceptional reliability, durability, and ease of use. With a standard magazine capacity of 17 rounds, the Glock 17 offers ample firepower. Its lightweight polymer frame, combined with a steel slide, ensures resilience and comfortable handling. Trusted by professionals and civilians alike, the Glock 17 is a popular choice for self-defense, law enforcement, and sport shooting due to its robust construction and impressive performance.

name: M700
description: The Remington M700 is an accurate and reliable bolt-action rifle widely used by hunters, law enforcement agencies, and military snipers around the world. With a reputation for precision, the M700 is available in various calibers and configurations to suit different shooting applications, from long-range target shooting to big game hunting.

name: Mosin-Nagant
description: The Mosin-Nagant Model 1891/30 is a bolt-action rifle that became the standard-issue rifle for the Soviet Union during World War II and beyond. Introduced in 1930, it is an updated version of the original Mosin-Nagant Model 1891, featuring improvements such as a five-round internal magazine and chambered in 7.62x54R cartridge. Renowned for its reliability, the Mosin-Nagant 1891/30 saw extensive service in various conflicts throughout the 20th century. Its affordability and availability have also made it popular among civilian shooters and collectors worldwide.

name: Mosin-Nagant (Sniper)
description: The sniper variant of the Mosin-Nagant Model 1891/30, employed by Soviet snipers during World War II, underwent several modifications for precision shooting. Notably, the rifle featured a modified bolt design to prevent interference with the telescopic sight and two holes in the upper receiver for mounting the sight securely. Despite these alterations, the sniper variant retained the same basic operating mechanism and chambering as the standard infantry rifle. With an extended effective range and enhanced accuracy, it played a vital role in Soviet sniping operations during the war.

name: Mossberg 590
description: The Mossberg 590 is a pump-action shotgun celebrated for its ruggedness and reliability. It features a 3-inch chamber and is available in various barrel lengths, typically ranging from 18.5 to 20 inches, catering to different preferences and applications. Designed primarily for defensive and tactical purposes, the Mossberg 590 is equipped with a sturdy receiver and a tang-mounted safety, ensuring quick and intuitive operation, particularly in high-pressure situations. Its dual extractors and twin action bars contribute to smooth cycling and dependable performance, even in harsh conditions.

name: MP5
description:
The MP5, short for Maschinenpistole 5, is an iconic submachine gun developed by the German firearms manufacturer Heckler & Koch (H&K). Introduced in the 1960s, it quickly gained recognition for its compact design, reliability, and versatility.
Originating from the successful roller-delayed blowback mechanism pioneered by H&K in the 1950s, the MP5 was a scaled-down version of the earlier MP4 submachine gun. It was initially designed for use by military and law enforcement units operating in confined spaces and urban environments, where maneuverability and close-range firepower were paramount. Throughout its history, the MP5 has undergone numerous iterations and variants, each tailored to specific operational requirements. These variants include different barrel lengths, stock configurations, and trigger group options. Notable variants include the MP5K, a compact version optimized for concealed carry and close-quarters combat, and the MP5SD, which features an integrated suppressor for reduced noise signature.

name: CQ A1
description: The Norinco CQ A1 is a Chinese replica of the American M4A1 rifle. This semi-automatic version is widely available in the civilian market due to its competitive pricing. Although it may have some surface finish shortcomings, this rifle is typically built with Mil-Spec tolerances.

name: M870
description: The Remington Model 870 is a classic pump-action shotgun known for its reliability, versatility, and widespread use in various applications such as hunting, sport shooting, and law enforcement. It features a robust and durable design, with a variety of configurations available to suit different preferences and needs. The Model 870 is celebrated for its smooth cycling action, solid construction, and proven performance, making it a popular choice among firearm enthusiasts worldwide.

name: Vz. 61 Skorpion
description: The Škorpion vz. 61, also known as the Vz. 61 Skorpion, is a prime example of a compact Czechoslovak submachine gun known for its reliability and versatility. Introduced in the 1960s, it quickly found its place among security forces and military units due to its compact size and firepower. Manufactured by Česká zbrojovka Uherský Brod between 1963 and 1979 under the official designation Samopal vzor 61, the Škorpion vz. 61 features a distinctive design with a folding stock and forward folding grip, making it exceptionally maneuverable in close-quarters combat situations. Chambered in the .32 ACP (7.65mm Browning) caliber, the Škorpion vz. 61 has a cyclic rate of fire of approximately 850 rounds per minute, providing a potent combination of firepower and controllability. Its compact size and lightweight construction make it suitable for various roles, including personal defense, special operations, and as a backup weapon for vehicle crews and pilots.

name: SKS
description: The SKS, originating in the Soviet Union, gained global prominence through widespread export and production. Notable for its fixed magazine and foldable bayonet, it lacked select-fire capability and had limited magazine capacity, leading to its replacement by the AK-47 in the Soviet Armed Forces during the 1950s. Despite this, the SKS continued to serve in various Soviet units for years. Soviet production occurred from 1949 to 1958 at the Tula Arsenal and from 1953 to 1954 at the Izhevsk Arsenal, resulting in approximately 2.7 million units. Additionally, millions more were produced under license in China and other Eastern Bloc countries during the Cold War. Its adaptability for guerrilla warfare made it popular among insurgent forces worldwide. Since 1988, the SKS has been widely available in the civilian market in North America, maintaining popularity for hunting and sporting activities.

name: Type 51
description: The Type 51 Tokarev is based on a steel-framed construction, which ensures durability and longevity. It uses a single-stack magazine that can hold eight rounds of 7.62x25mm Tokarev ammunition. The pistol operates on a simple blowback mechanism, which is known for its reliability and ease of maintenance.

name: AK/AKM Dust Cover (late)
description: A top dust cover for the AK/AKM series of rifles.

name: AK-100 Series Dust Cover
description: This is a dust cover for a stamped AK receiver, specifically the original Russian AK-100 model. It is compatible with Saiga and Arsenal rifles.

name: M4 Upper Receiver
description: An upper receiver for the M4 series of rifles. The Picatinny rail allows for the attachment of optics and various additional devices.

name: MK18 A4 Upper Receiver
description: The Daniel Defense A4 Upper Receiver Assembly is designed for personalized construction. Crafted with precision in a cutting-edge manufacturing facility and supported by a satisfaction guarantee, this product is ready for any custom build.

name: Picatinny Dust Cover
description: The PDC is an aluminum dust cover that serves as a replacement for AK/AKM assault rifles. It is equipped with a milled Picatinny scope mount and features a patented retention mechanism that allows for manual adjustment. This ensures a consistent retention of sighting zero and allows for a straightforward and rapid drop-in installation.

name: Glock 17 Slide
description: The standard slide designed for Glock 9x19 pistols. It serves as a crucial component of the firearm's upper assembly.

name: Tyton Glock 17 Slide
description: A premium slide specifically crafted for the Glock 17 pistol. It offers enhanced performance while also boasting a visually striking design.

name: M16A1 Upper Receiver
description: The M16A1 Upper Receiver is a vital component of the M16A1 rifle, housing the barrel and operating mechanism. It features a fixed carrying handle with an integrated rear sight, providing durability and essential functionality to the firearm.

name: MP5
description: The MP5 receiver is the core component of Heckler & Koch's renowned submachine gun. It houses critical parts like the bolt assembly and trigger group, ensuring reliable performance in various tactical situations. Built with precision and durability, it embodies the iconic status of the MP5, preferred by military, law enforcement, and civilian users worldwide.

name: MP5SD
description: The MP5SD receiver is a specialized variant of Heckler & Koch's submachine gun, designed for stealth operations with integrated sound suppression. It retains the essential components while incorporating features to support the integral suppressor. Precision baffles and ports minimize muzzle report and flash signature, making it ideal for covert missions. Trusted by elite units, the MP5SD receiver epitomizes silent yet potent submachine gun technology.

name: N17 Reptile EDC Slide
description: The N17 Reptile EDC Slide is a high-performance upgrade for the Glock 17 handgun, designed to improve both its functionality and aesthetics. It features a sleek, reptilian scale-like serration pattern that improves grip and manipulation in various conditions.

name: P40 Warhawk Slide
description: This slide for the Glock 17 draws inspiration from World War II with its captivating design, featuring authentic nose art from the legendary P40 Warhawk aircraft. It showcases meticulous CNC-machined rivet markings, adding an extra level of detail and character to the slide.

name: Dog Leg Rail
description: A modern dog leg rail dust cover for the AK series of rifles.

name: TT-33 Slide
description: The TT-33 Tokarev slide originated in the Soviet Union and is made of steel, embodying the rugged reliability synonymous with Soviet firearm design. The slide features distinct serrations at the rear, designed to enhance grip and manipulation under various conditions. It houses the barrel and recoil spring assembly, orchestrating the seamless cycling of the pistol's action. The TT-33 is renowned for its robust construction and timeless design.

name: Type 51 Slide
description: The Type 51 Tokarev slide, originating from China, is made of steel, making it durable and resilient. The serrations at the rear offer enhanced grip during manipulation, and the slide itself houses the barrel and recoil spring assembly, facilitating the cycling of the pistol's action. Its robust construction and straightforward design ensure reliable functionality and ease of operation.

name: Glock 17 ZPS.6 Slide
description: The ZPS.6 combines sleek aesthetics with enhanced performance. Constructed from high-quality stainless steel, this precision-engineered slide offers improved durability and reliability.

name: B-33 Rail
description: The B-33 is a dust cover with an integrated Picatinny rail that is compatible with all models of AK assault rifles.

name: Z17 Citadel Slide
description: The ZEV Z17 is a high-quality aftermarket slide designed for the Glock 17 pistol, offering enhanced performance and customization options.

name: AK-74M Polymer Stock
description: The AK-74M Polymer Stock is made of durable synthetic polymer and is compatible with AK-100, AK-105, AK-74M, Saiga, and Yunker rifles.

name: AK-74N Wooden Stock
description: A typical wooden stock for the AK-47, AK-74M and AK-74N.

name: AK-47/AKM Wooden Stock
description: A wooden stock that is compatible with AK-47 and AKM rifles.

name: AKMSN Foldable Stock
description: A foldable AKMSN stock designed to be light and compact.

name: CTR Cheek Riser
description: Raises cheek weld 3/4 inch in height.

name: AR-15 Archangel Low-Profile Buttstock
description: The Low-profile design is lightweight and compact but still allows for quick weapon handling/accurate shooting. It includes over-molded quick detach sling swivel cup mounting points and slots for standard web slings. The stock is constructed using high-strength carbon fiber and glass-reinforced black polymer.

name: SKS Strikeforce TactLite Stock
description: The TactLite Adjustable Stock stands out as one of the lightest six-position adjustable stocks available. Beyond its lightweight design, this innovative stock prioritizes functionality by reducing snag points and providing a secure fit. Crafted from durable DuPont Extreme Temperature Glass Reinforced Polymer, it ensures resilience in diverse environmental conditions.

name: AR-15 M401 Nylon Stock
description: Constructed from premium nylon, this stock features a comfortable rubber-covered butt plate and rugged construction for extended durability. Its sleek design not only enhances aesthetics but also provides a secure grip in combat scenarios. The stock features a sturdy nylon lever with a metal pin for exceptional strength, along with a built-in ring for convenient sling attachment.

name: M4 Buffer Tube
description: A receiver extension compatible with the AR-15 platform. It provides a secure mounting point for the stock and aids in mitigating recoil, resulting in enhanced shooting comfort and improved control.

name: M4 Standard Buttstock
description: A standard Colt M4 buttstock compatible with the AR-15 weapon platform.

name: CZ Bren 2  Standard Stock Type 1
description: The genuine CZ folding stock for Bren 2 models delivers exceptional versatility with both folding and collapsible features. Compatible with 5.56x45 and 7.62x39 Bren 2 configurations, this stock enhances portability without sacrificing stability, providing a dynamic and compact solution for your firearm needs.

name: CZ Bren 2  Standard Stock Type 2
description: The genuine CZ folding stock for Bren 2 models delivers exceptional versatility with both folding and collapsible features. Compatible with 5.56x45 and 7.62x39 Bren 2 configurations, this stock enhances portability without sacrificing stability, providing a dynamic and compact solution for your firearm needs.

name: DD Adjustable Buttstock
description: The Daniel Defense adjustable buttstock is made of a unique blend of glass-infused polymers and finished with soft-touch rubber in strategic areas. It is precision-formed for Mil-Spec receiver extensions, minimizing forward or lateral play that is often found in other buttstocks. name: Extended Rubber Butt-Pad
description: The Extended Rubber Butt-Pad is crafted with a robust rubber material to provide improved grip on the shoulder and enhance impact/drop mitigation.

name: H-S Precision Pro-Series 2000
description: The H-S Precision Pro-Series 2000 M24 A1 Tactical Stock is a precision-engineered upgrade for the Remington M700 rifle. It is designed for durability and accuracy, with a classic ergonomic design that offers good grip and maneuverability.

name: HK G36 Stock
description: Effortlessly integrate the HK G36 folding stock into your CZ Bren 2. precision-machined aluminum stock adapter, paired with a high-performance polymer shell deflector, creates one of the most streamlined and comprehensive stock options for the Bren 2 platform. name: M870 Stock (OD Green)
description: Made from durable rubber, this stock provides a comfortable and secure grip, improving control with each shot and ensuring reliable performance for extended use.

name: AR-15 SOPMOD Stock
description: A preferred stock among USSOCOM soldiers for the AR-15 weapon platform, offering enhanced comfort and optimal fit for the operator. This stock ensures durability, reliability, and improved weapon handling.

name: M700 Hunter Stock
description: The Hunter 700L Stock for the Remington M700 rifle is made with a reinforced polymer and an anodized aluminum bedding block. It offers complete adjustability in length of pull, comb height, and improved ergonomics.

name: AR-15 CTR Stock
description: A versatile stock option for the AR-15 platform. With its streamlined design and robust construction, it provides a solid and comfortable shooting experience while shielding the release latch to prevent accidental activation, ensuring optimal control and safety.

name: AK MOE Stock
description: The Magpul MOE AK Stock is a fixed stock designed for rifles with stamped receivers. It integrates Magpul's innovative design and construction into the AK platform. The MOE AK Stock features a unique wedge block fit inspired by the Zhukov-S Stock. It includes internal storage, strategically positioned QD sling swivels, and a rubber butt pad for effective recoil absorption and secure positioning.

name: AR15 MOE Stock
description: The MOE Carbine Stock - Mil-Spec model is a replacement buttstock for AR15/M16 carbines that use Mil-Spec-sized receiver extension tubes. Its streamlined A-frame profile is designed for light, fast action and avoids snagging. The release latch is also shielded to prevent accidental activation.

name: M590 SGA Stock
description: The SGA Stock is a versatile buttstock designed for Mossberg 500/590/590A1 12-gauge shotguns. It offers enhanced adjustability and ergonomics, with an ambidextrous design that allows for easy customization to suit individual preferences.

name: M870 SGA Stock
description: The SGA Stock is a versatile buttstock, offering customizable options to enhance the Remington 870 12 gauge shotgun. The stock is equipped with a spacer system for adjusting the length of pull, enhanced grip ergonomics, a recoil-reducing butt-pad, and the choice of optional cheek risers for compatibility with optics or raised sights.

name: SKS Sabertooth MKII Stock
description: The SABERTOOTH MK-II boasts a robust, aircraft-grade aluminum build, meticulously machined for straightforward installation across a wide range of SKS variants. Its design promotes versatility, allowing users to personalize their rifles with standard AR-15 pistol grips and buttstocks. Equipped with a sturdy aluminum quad rail handguard, it provides limitless possibilities for accessory mounting. Compatible with diverse SKS models and magazine types, it incorporates a removable dust cap block for effortless maintenance. Additionally, the design incorporates a rear recess to accommodate an optional top-rail mount.

name: M870 Stock Adapter
description: This stock adapter and pistol grip system allows for attaching AR-style collapsible stocks and pistol grips to the M870 shotgun.

name: M700 MOD*X Stock
description: The A*B Arms MOD*X GEN III is a lightweight, ergonomically designed stock for the Remington M700, ideal for military, law enforcement, and hunting enthusiasts.

name: Mosin-Nagant Wooden Stock (Carbine)
description: The Mosin Carbine Wooden Stock is a classic accessory for the Mosin-Nagant rifle, which has been used in various military conflicts throughout history. It is crafted from durable wood, enhancing the rifle's aesthetics and providing a comfortable grip for users.

name: Mosin-Nagant Folding Stock
description: This folding stock allows for improved portability and ease of transportation. The product is made of naturally dried wood and solid steel components, giving it an old-school look.

name: Mosin-Nagant Wooden Stock (Rifle)

name: M590 Stock

name: MP5 A3 Stock

Its retractable design offers adjustable length-of-pull for versatility, while its durable construction ensures reliability in the field. Upgrade your MP5 with this genuine surplus stock for enhanced performance and aesthetics.

name: Mosin-Nagant Archangel Stock
description: Engineered to enhance the performance of Mosin-Nagant rifles with its modern and durable design. It is made from rugged polymer material in an olive drab color, and offers a tactical and functional upgrade. The adjustable cheek rest and length of pull provide personalized comfort, while the overall design includes ergonomic enhancements for improved handling.

name: M870 Express Stock
description: This stock combines classic aesthetics with reliable performance. It is crafted with durable materials, offering a comfortable grip and a timeless look.

name: Recoil Reducing Pad
description: The Rubber Shock Absorbing Recoil Pad is a deluxe-style pad designed with ergonomic features to reduce recoil. It has a smart slip-on sleeve design with lip reinforcement.

name: SKS Stock
description: The SKS wooden stock is a hallmark feature of the Soviet-designed Simonov semi-automatic rifle. Crafted from durable hardwood, it ensures a stable and comfortable grip for the shooter. Its traditional design not only offers an aesthetic appeal but also withstands diverse environmental conditions. Typically boasting a smooth finish, it enhances both appearance and functionality, rendering it a favored option among firearms enthusiasts for its enduring charm and dependable performance.

name: MP5/HK33/53 Stock
description: Machined from solid billet aircraft aluminum, the stock adapter includes an integrated buffer and offers six-position adjustability for length. Its non-reciprocating cheek piece, with additional height options available, aligns the shooter's eye with optic sights. Enhanced ergonomics contribute to improved recoil management, facilitating fast and accurate fire, even in fully automatic mode. Compatible with HK MP5, HK33, and HK53 models, as well as their clones.

name: Vz. 61 Wire Stock
description: A folding stock crafted for the Vz. 61 Skorpion submachine gun. Constructed from durable steel wire, it offers easy storage and deployment. Despite its lightweight design, the stock ensures stability and control during shooting.

name: M700 Stock
description: Crafted from premium wood, this stock enhances the rifle's aesthetics and provides a comfortable, ergonomic grip.

name: AK PT-1 Stock
description: The PT-1 telescopic skeleton stock is designed for the AK series of rifles and features a rubber butt pad and cheek. It is positioned in the standard location where AK stocks typically fold to the side, allowing for tailored adjustments to the shooter's tasks and individual physique.

name: AK PT-3 Stock
description: The telescopic PT-3 stock is designed for use with the AK series of rifles. It is milled and equipped with a rubber back and cheek pad. The stock is installed in the standard location where AK stocks typically fold to the side. It features a length adjustment mechanism with a range of 5 cm and a customizable cheek rest.

name: AK Zhukov Stock
description: The Magpul Zhukov-S Stock is a folding stock solution for modern AK rifles. Unlike traditional AK stocks, the Zhukov-S Stock is foldable and collapsible, and includes QD sling mounts, customizable Cheek Risers, and a shock-absorbing rubber butt-pad for improved grip and comfort.

name: M590 Barrel - 18.5"
description: The 18.5” security barrel with a bead sight is a versatile solution for 12 gauge Mossberg 500 and Maverick 88 6-shot models. It has a cylinder bore and matte-blued finish, optimizing it for close-range engagements and rapid target acquisition. The bead sight enhances aiming precision, making it ideal for home defense and tactical applications.

It has a bead sight for quick target acquisition, making it suitable for various shooting scenarios. The smoothbore and matte-blued finish provide reliability and durability.

It has a bead sight for quick target acquisition, making it suitable for various shooting scenarios. The smoothbore and matte-blued finish provide reliability and durability. name: M870 Barrel - 18.5"
description: Crafted from high-quality steel and finished with a non-glare black coating, this barrel is designed specifically for Remington 870 12 gauge shotguns. It offers enhanced versatility and accuracy with its 18.5" length, pre-installed front ramp sight, and compatibility with Rem choke tubes.

description: This AR-15 barrel boasts a length of 508mm and is specifically crafted for the AR-15 weapon platform. It offers compatibility with various 5.56x45mm cartridges, providing increased accuracy for your firearm.

description: This barrel is typically made of high-grade steel for durability and resistance to wear. It is designed to handle the pressures generated by the 7.62x25mm Tokarev cartridge and has a rifled bore to stabilize the projectiles.

name: Type 51 Threaded Barrel

Threaded barrels are designed to withstand the pressures of the 7.62x25mm Tokarev cartridge while maintaining the same precision engineering as standard barrels, providing consistent accuracy and reliability.

name: M700 Threaded Barrel - 18"
description: An 18” threaded barrel for the Remington M700, which is both compact and customizable. The threaded muzzle enables easy attachment of accessories such as suppressors or muzzle brakes, making it a versatile option for those who prioritize maneuverability and personalized firearm setups.

name: M700 Suppressed Barrel - 20"
description: This 20” barrel for the Remington M700 comes with a built-in suppressor that features a titanium tube and a single-piece monolithic core. The suppressor is available in two caliber options: .308 or 300 Blackout.

name: M700 Barrel - 22"
description: This 22” barrel for the Remington M700 is precision-crafted for exceptional accuracy and adaptability. Its threaded design allows for muzzle accessories, striking a balance between maneuverability and bullet velocity. This barrel is ideal for hunting and precision shooting, offering both reliability and performance.

name: M700 VTR Barrel -  22"
description: A 22” barrel for the Remington M700 with a unique triangular profile and built-in muzzle brake. This design delivers both on aesthetics and accuracy, providing a balanced mix of maneuverability and bullet velocity.

Crafted from high-quality Chromoly steel alloys, each barrel undergoes a meticulous one-at-a-time process to ensure superb accuracy.

name: Mosin-Nagant Barrel - 730mm

name: F-1 Charging Handle

name: SCH 5.56 Charging Handle (DDC)
description: The Geissele Super Charging Handle (SCH) offers exceptional reliability and smooth operation. Its Desert Dirt Color (DDC) finish adds a touch of style to any compatible firearm.

name: AR-15 GRIP-N-RIP Charging Handle
description: The GRIP-N-RIP AR-15 Charging Handle is an ergonomic and durable upgrade for the AR-15 rifle and other compatible firearms. With its enhanced grip design, this charging handle provides improved control and ease of use during weapon manipulation.

name: HK MP5 Cocking Handle
description: The HK MP5 cocking handle is an essential part of the submachine gun's design, providing manual operation to charge the weapon and chamber a round. Located on the left side of the receiver, it offers ergonomic access for ambidextrous use, enhancing handling and control

name: Standard GI Charging Handle
description: A reliable and versatile charging handle designed for use with the AR-15 weapon platform. Built to industry-standard specifications, this charging handle ensures smooth and efficient operation, allowing for quick and easy manipulation of the bolt carrier group.

name: Vz. 61 Charging Knobs
description: The charging knob of the Vz. 61 Skorpion submachine gun is used to retract and release the bolt mechanism, streamlining the process of loading and chambering ammunition.

name: AKM Gas Tube
description: A standard gas tube compatible with the AK-74 series of rifles. It channels gas from the fired cartridge to a mechanism that disposes of the spent case and inserts a new cartridge into the chamber.

name: AK-74 Gas Tube
description: The gas tube of the AK-74 rifle is a crucial component that is situated above the barrel. It operates the rifle's gas-operated action by channeling propellant gasses to drive the piston, cycle the action, and aid in the extraction and ejection of spent cartridges.

name: JPGS-6 Gas Block
description: The JPGS-6 model is dial-adjustable small bore design intended facilitate easy transitioning between suppressed and unsuppressed fire on large-frame rifles.

name: DD MK12 Low Profile Gas Block
description: Crafted by Daniel Defense, this gas block ensures reliable gas regulation for optimal performance and accuracy. With its low-profile design, it offers a sleek and streamlined appearance, reducing weight and improving overall firearm balance.

name: M4A1 Standard Gas Block
description: A standard gas block for the M4A1 carbine. As an essential component, it effectively regulates the flow of gas from the fired cartridge to ensure proper cycling of the weapon's mechanism. It also features a front sight post.

name: Vulcan M1
description: A device engineered to enhance the performance of 5.56x45mm caliber firearms. Designed by ANTREG with efficiency in mind, this muzzle brake effectively reduces recoil and muzzle rise, allowing for improved accuracy and faster target acquisition. name: B&T MP5 Flash Hider
description: This flash hider easily slides onto the end of the 3-lug barrel and secures with a simple 1/4 turn. Its quick-detach feature allows for effortless installation and removal with a flick of the wrist, providing convenience and ease of use.

name: 3-Lug threaded HK MP5
description: The Wyssen Defence 3 Lug Adapter enables the mounting of Heckler & Koch MP5/SP5 and Wyssen Defence WD9 muzzle devices, such as suppressors, flash hiders, and silencers, onto 9mm Luger caliber firearms with muzzle threads.

name: Tactical Muzzle Brake
description: This muzzle device is designed to significantly reduce recoil. It extends about 2.75 inches beyond the barrel's end and has a matte black finish, improving the appearance of any shotgun while also providing better firearm control and faster follow-up shots.

name: A2 Flash Hider
description: A flash hider for 5.56x45mm caliber weapons. Manufactured by Colt and designed to be compatible with the AR-15 weapon platform. It effectively reduces muzzle flash, providing improved visibility and reducing the potential for visual disruption during rapid-fire or low-light shooting scenarios.

name: XM177E2 Moderator Flash Hider
description: This early flash hider for 5.56x45mm caliber weapons effectively reduces muzzle flash, improving shooter visibility and reducing the risk of giving away their position in low-light conditions. Originally manufactured by Colt in early 1967, this particular model was consistently utilized on the XM177E2. However, production of the Moderators by Colt ceased in the mid-1970s, following a ruling by the ATF categorizing the device as a sound "suppressor."

name: Glock 17 Comp Weight Compensator
description: This low-profile addition seamlessly integrates with the firearm's design, eliminating the need for a threaded barrel. The Comp Weight enhances aesthetics and functions as an effective compensator, directing pressure downward to reduce recoil and enhance accuracy, minimizing muzzle flip for improved performance.

name: CZ Bren 2 Standard Flash Hider
description: Spiral three-prong flash hider with the option for easy thread-on attachment of a sound suppressor featuring ROTEX-V mounting interface. The unique design of the flash hider's prongs ensures self-tightening with each shot fired.

name: DD Extended Flash Suppressor
description: The Daniel Defense Flash Suppressor is designed to reduce muzzle flash. Since it’s manufactured from aerospace grade 17-4 stainless steel and finished with a salt bath nitride, there is minimal chance of corrosion.

name: Tactical Muzzle Break
description: This muzzle brake is made of durable aluminum with an anodized black finish and is designed to significantly reduce recoil during competition shooting.

name: M4QD Flash Hider
description: A flash hider engineered by Knights Armament Company (KAC). Designed for 5.56x45mm caliber firearms, particularly the M4 and AR-15 platforms, this device effectively mitigates muzzle flash, reducing the shooter's visual signature and enhancing target acquisition. It also serves as a platform for attaching a sound suppressor.

name: Mosin-Nagant Howling Raven Muzzle Brake
description: This muzzle brake is designed specifically for the original Mosin-Nagant 91/30 model and is intended to fit snugly around the front sight post. It is secured in place by three brass set screws. Made in America from steel with a black oxide coating, this muzzle brake significantly reduces recoil.

name: Mosin-Nagant Tanker Muzzle Brake
description: The M44 Tanker-style Bolt-on Muzzle Brake is made of durable steel and has a robust construction with a heat-treated, erosion-resistant black oxide finish. It has side and top ports that minimize muzzle flip, recoil, and barrel whip, enhancing shooting stability and control by efficiently redirecting gases.

name: MP5 3 Lug Adapter
description: The HK 3-Lug Adapter features internal threading with 1/2 X 28 threads, enabling attachment to existing 1/2 X 28 threaded applications. This adapter facilitates the addition of 3-lug attachments, including flash hiders, compensators, suppressors, and silencers, to the male end. Renowned for its precision machining, this adapter represents the highest quality available in the market.

name: MP5 Muzzle Cap
description: The MP5 Muzzle Cap is a protective accessory designed to cover and safeguard the muzzle of the MP5 firearm. It helps prevent damage to the muzzle threads and keeps debris out of the barrel when the firearm is not in use.

name: PCAM4-72
description: The PCAM4-72 features a triple baffle design, which significantly reduces recoil. Precision-canted side vents eliminate muzzle climb, ensuring minimal movement and reduced dust signature when prone. Built for durability and impact resistance, it features a lightweight design that can withstand combat conditions without rapid erosion.

name: Remington Salvo 12 Choke Adapter
description: The Salvo 12 Choke Adapter functions as both a choke and a suppressor adapter. It enables compatibility between your shotgun and Salvo 12 suppressor, resulting in quieter shooting while also providing customizable choke options for improved performance and versatility.

name: 3 Prong Flash Hider
description: Three-pronged flash suppressor designed for 5.56mm SIG SAUER rifles.

name: MCX 3 Prong Flash Hider
description: Crafted from high-quality steel and coated in a sleek black finish, the Sig Sauer MCX 3-Prong Flash Hider is a fast-attach suppressor that minimizes flash and muzzle climb, thus enhancing the firearm’s performance.

name: SKS Muzzle Brake Adapter
description: This SKS adapter with M24 thread allows you to mount various muzzle brakes suitable for the 7.62x39 caliber. Simply mount the adapter on the barrel of the carbine and secure it with two screws behind the front sight.

name: SRD762-QD Muzzle Brake
description: The SRD762-QD Taper-Lok Muzzle Brake self-centers the firearm and suppressor, which reduces group dispersion and improves accuracy.

name: SRD762-QD Flash Hider
description: The SRD762-QD Flash Hider optimizes alignment, improves accuracy, and reduces point of impact shift. It is low-profile yet very effective at reducing muzzle flash.

name: SRD762-QD Taper-Lok Muzzle Brake
description: The SRD762-QD Taper-Lok Muzzle Brake self-centers the firearm and suppressor, which reduces group dispersion and improves accuracy.

name: Surefire FH556RC Flash Hider 5.56x45
description: Designed to minimize muzzle flash and recoil. Manufactured by Surefire, this flash hider is specifically engineered for 5.56x45mm caliber rifles. name: X-Factor Choke
description: This precision-engineered accessory enhances shotgun performance. Its ported design reduces muzzle jump and recoil, allowing for faster follow-up shots and increased accuracy. Featuring an Improved Cylinder constriction pattern, it guarantees an optimal spread tailored for close-range targets, rendering it well-suited for hunting and tactical scenarios demanding swift, precise shooting.

name: DTK-1 Muzzle Brake
description: The DTK-1 muzzle brake is specifically designed for AK rifles with a thread size of 24x1.5. It effectively reduces recoil and compensates for barrel movement. Additionally, the crown is designed to break glass.

name: DTK-2 Muzzle Brake
description: The DTK-2 muzzle brake compensator is designed for use with 7.62mm and 5.45mm AK carbines, effectively reducing recoil and compensating for muzzle rise.

name: BANISH 45 Suppressor
description: Designed for calibers ranging from .45 ACP to rimfire, the Banish 45 is a versatile and modular handgun/pistol suppressor. It is compatible with various pistons, making it user-serviceable and efficient. Reducing noise by 36db, this suppressor provides a quiet and adaptable shooting experience across multiple calibers.

name: HK MP5SD 9mm Suppressor
description: The Heckler & Koch MP5SD 9mm Aluminum Suppressor, Demo, is a rare factory original from HK in Germany. Constructed from aluminum and finished in black, it measures 12" in length, with an outside diameter of 1.575" and a weight of 1.05 lbs. It attaches to the MP5SD barrel using M18x1 metric threads and is acclaimed as the quietest HK suppressor ever produced.

name: QDSS NT4 Suppressor
description: A high-quality suppressor designed for 5.56mm caliber weapons. Manufactured by Knights Armament Company (KAC), this suppressor offers exceptional noise reduction, enhancing stealth and minimizing muzzle flash.

name: Mosin-Nagant Bramit Suppressor
description: This suppressor was created In June 1940 by the Mitin brothers. Named BraMit (short for Brothers Mitin), it was attached to the barrel in the same way as a bayonet, with a length of 147mm and a diameter of 32mm. In December 1940, after successful tests, BraMit was accepted for service, and serial production began in the second half of 1941.

name: PBS-01 Suppressor
description: Original Soviet suppressor for AK-47, AKM, and M70 rifles chambered in 7.62x39mm, including a sight for shooting with subsonic ammunition.

name: PBS-04 Suppressor
description: This is one of the most acknowledged suppressors of the AK family of rifles. Unlike the PBS-1, this suppressor is designed for the 5.45x39mm cartridge.

name: Salvo 12 Suppressor
description: The SilencerCo Salvo 12 is a shotgun suppressor compatible with most pump-action and semi-automatic shotguns and nearly all commercially available ammunition. Its modular design allows users to adjust sound, weight, and length by adding or removing sections as needed.

name: SLH762-QD Suppressor
description: The SLH series rifle suppressors feature the latest Clutch-LOK QD mounting system and an internal multi-flow path, which prioritizes sound reduction while reducing up to 50% of toxic fumes venting through the ejection port.

name: 762-SD Suppressor
description: The AAC 762-SDN-6 is a fast-attach silencer designed for 7.62x51mm ammo, as well as smaller calibers like .300BLK and 5.56mm. It is compact, versatile, and extremely durable for full-time silencer use on select guns. The silencer provides a 98.9% reduction in muzzle sound pressure, prioritizing the preservation of the shooter's hearing and minimizing the muzzle blast signature.

name: DTSS Suppressor
description: The DTSS Suppressor is designed to improve accuracy and reduce impact shift between suppressed and unsuppressed firing. Desert Tech sound suppressors can improve rifle accuracy by 1/4 MOA or better. This is achieved through weldless mono-core designs that efficiently strip away gas, minimizing disturbance and maximizing projectile stability at the muzzle exit.

name: SOCOM556 RC1 Suppressor
description: A military-grade silencer crafted from a durable blend of stainless steel and Inconel 718. The suppressor provides premium sound reduction, eliminates first-round muzzle flash, and minimizes dust signature. It is specifically designed for 5.56mm rifles, ensuring lasting durability that may even outlast the host barrel.

The suppressor is typically made of durable materials like steel or aluminum and attaches to the threaded barrel of the Type 51 Tokarev, effectively reducing the sound signature of each shot. This accessory improves the pistol's versatility, making it suitable for applications where reduced noise and flash are desired.

name: Ultima Suppressor

name: M700 Thread Cap
